  "content": "### Privacy Policy\n\n**Effective Date**: August 6, 2025  \n**Version**: 0.2.1\n\nMetaRune respects your privacy and believes in data minimalism. This Privacy Policy outlines what data we collect (if any), how it is used, and your responsibilities as a user.\n\n---\n\n#### 1. **Data Collection Overview**\nMetaRune does **not collect, store, or process any sensitive personal data**. However, some limited technical data is handled through third-party services for authentication and performance monitoring:\n\n##### a. **Firebase Authentication**\n- We use Firebase Authentication to allow users to sign in securely.\n- Firebase stores **user email addresses** as part of its core functionality.\n- MetaRune itself does **not store or access** these emails.\n- Authentication data is managed by **Google Firebase**, and subject to their [Privacy Policy](https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy).\n\n##### b. **Firebase Analytics & Crashlytics**\n- We use Firebase Analytics and Crashlytics **only to monitor crashes, detect bugs, and improve performance**.\n- These services may collect **anonymized device data** such as OS version, crash logs, or general technical performance.\n- We do **not use these tools to profile, track, or identify users**.\n\n---\n\n#### 2. **No Sensitive Data Stored**\nMetaRune does **not** collect or store:\n- Names, phone numbers, government-issued IDs\n- Wallet private keys or seed phrases\n- Biometric data or signed credentials\n- Behavioral analytics or personal preferences\n\n---\n\n#### 3. **Local-Only Identity and Key Management**\n- All keys, identities, and credentials are created and stored **locally** on your device.\n- MetaRune has **no access to your cryptographic data**.\n- If your keys are lost or deleted, they are **irrecoverable**.\n\n---\n\n#### 4. **No Tracking or Cookies**\n- We do **not** use cookies, web beacons, or fingerprinting techniques.\n- We do **not** share or sell data with third parties.\n\n---\n\n#### 5. **Third-Party Decentralized Integrations**\nMetaRune may interface with third-party decentralized identity systems (e.g., W3C DIDs, Verifiable Credentials). These are:\n- Fully opt-in by the user\n- Managed externally from MetaRune\n- Governed by their own protocols and policies\n\n---\n\n#### 6. **Childrenâ€™s Privacy**\n- MetaRune is intended for users **22 years and older**.\n- We do not knowingly collect information from users below this age.\n\n---\n\n#### 7. **Policy Updates**\nThis policy may change over time to reflect updates in technology or regulation. When we make changes, we will update the version and date shown above. Continued use of the app indicates your acceptance of the updated policy.\n\n---\n\n#### 8. **Contact**\nIf you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, you can reach us at:  \nðŸ“§ **MetaRune@gmail.com**\n\n---\n\nÂ© 2025 MetaRune. All Rights Reserved."
